   8 TypeDefinition = namedtuple('TypeDefinition', 'name,included_types,excluded_types')
   9 """
  10 This class is used to define types that can be used as value in the
  11 :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.types_mapping` property.
  12 The ``name`` should be descriptive and match the key it is going to be assigned
  13 to.
  14 A value that is validated against such definition must be an instance of any of
  15 the types contained in ``included_types`` and must not match any of the types
  16 contained in ``excluded_types``.
  17 """
  18

  20 def compare_paths_lt(x, y):
  21     min_length = min(len(x), len(y))
  22 
  23     if x[:min_length] == y[:min_length]:
  24         return len(x) == min_length
  25 
  26     for i in range(min_length):
  27         a, b = x[i], y[i]
  28 
  29         for _type in (_int_types, _str_type, tuple):
  30             if isinstance(a, _type):
  31                 if isinstance(b, _type):
  32                     break
  33                 else:
  34                     return True
  35 
  36         if a == b:
  37             continue
  38         elif a < b:
  39             return True
  40         else:
  41             return False
  42 
  43     raise RuntimeError
  44

  46 def drop_item_from_tuple(t, i):
  47     return t[:i] + t[i + 1 :]
  48

  50 def get_Validator_class():
  51     global Validator
  52     if 'Validator' not in globals():
  53         from cerberus.validator import Validator
  54     return Validator
  55

  57 def mapping_hash(schema):
  58     return hash(mapping_to_frozenset(schema))
  59 
  60 
  61 def mapping_to_frozenset(mapping):
  62     """ Be aware that this treats any sequence type with the equal members as
  63         equal. As it is used to identify equality of schemas, this can be
  64         considered okay as definitions are semantically equal regardless the
  65         container type. """
  66 
  67     aggregation = {}
  68 
  69     for key, value in mapping.items():
  70         if isinstance(value, Mapping):
  71             aggregation[key] = mapping_to_frozenset(value)
  72         elif isinstance(value, Sequence):
  73             value = list(value)
  74             for i, item in enumerate(value):
  75                 if isinstance(item, Mapping):
  76                     value[i] = mapping_to_frozenset(item)
  77             aggregation[key] = tuple(value)
  78         elif isinstance(value, Set):
  79             aggregation[key] = frozenset(value)
  80         else:
  81             aggregation[key] = value
  82 
  83     return frozenset(aggregation.items())
  84 
  85 
  86 def quote_string(value):
  87     if isinstance(value, _str_type):
  88         return '"%s"' % value
  89     else:
  90         return value

  93 class readonly_classproperty(property):
  94     def __get__(self, instance, owner):
  95         return super(readonly_classproperty, self).__get__(owner)
  96 
  97     def __set__(self, instance, value):
  98         raise RuntimeError('This is a readonly class property.')
  99 
 100     def __delete__(self, instance):
 101         raise RuntimeError('This is a readonly class property.')

 104 def validator_factory(name, bases=None, namespace={}):
 105     """ Dynamically create a :class:`~cerberus.Validator` subclass.
 106         Docstrings of mixin-classes will be added to the resulting
 107         class' one if ``__doc__`` is not in :obj:`namespace`.
 108 
 109     :param name: The name of the new class.
 110     :type name: :class:`str`
 111     :param bases: Class(es) with additional and overriding attributes.
 112     :type bases: :class:`tuple` of or a single :term:`class`
 113     :param namespace: Attributes for the new class.
 114     :type namespace: :class:`dict`
 115     :return: The created class.
 116     """
 117     Validator = get_Validator_class()
 118 
 119     if bases is None:
 120         bases = (Validator,)
 121     elif isinstance(bases, tuple):
 122         bases += (Validator,)
 123     else:
 124         bases = (bases, Validator)
 125 
 126     docstrings = [x.__doc__ for x in bases if x.__doc__]
 127     if len(docstrings) > 1 and '__doc__' not in namespace:
 128         namespace.update({'__doc__': '\n'.join(docstrings)})
 129 
 130     return type(name, bases, namespace)
